The paper discusses methods for generating events with pre-defined probabilities, which is a common problem in cryptography and simulation of systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of probability distribution functions, which is a common topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses generating probabilistic sequences, which could fall under the sub-categories of Data Mining (cs.DM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
